    <h4>Basic Example</h4>
    <p>Tree menu's are used often in wiki or documentation user interfaces in order to show page hierarchy to the user. The menu is expandable and allows for ease-of-use.</p>
    <h5>Important Settings</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>Tree menu list items with children are identified with the <code>.is-expandable</code> class</li>
        <li>To have a menu open by default, use the <code>.is-expanded</code> class on the menu list item</li>
        <li>Display active list items with the <code>.is-active</code> class</li>
    </ul>
